item.title: Im new and want to code but idk wtf is going on
item.dc:creator: @Marine5287 Marine5287
item.description:
@Marine5287 wrote:

Well first of all, go in your control panel>Programs>Programs and Features. Now uninstall all the java products, then go to java.com and download that. Then go to http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/index.html and scroll down like an inch or two and you’ll see “Download JDK”. Now second of all, whatever you’re trying to open, right click it and click “edit” and look at something that looks like this “C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_11\bin\javac.exe” *.java" and in the jdk1.6.0_11 you’d replace the 11 with 24 and it should work.
